Context: The Student Association represents all George Brown College students and is located at 200 King St. East, Room 147 (Toronto ON M5A 3W8), 142 Kendal Ave, Room e100 (Toronto ON M5R 1M3), and 51 Dockside Dr., Room 033 (Toronto ON M5A 1B6). Their contact numbers are St. James: 416-415-5000 ext. 2455, Casa Loma: 416-415-5000 ext. 4730, Waterfront: 416-415-5000 ext. 5360, and Toronto Metropolitan University: 416-415-5000 ext. 4049. Their services are offered to full-time students only, and the hours of operation vary by location: St. James, Casa Loma and Waterfront - Monday to Thursday 9:15 a.m. to 4:45 p.m., Friday 9:15 a.m. to 3 p.m., and Toronto Metropolitan University - check the website for times based on semester. The services offered include learning more about the Student Association, land acknowledgment, and staying informed about application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, and tours. To contact them, you can call 416-415-2000 or email ask.george@georgebrown.ca. They also have a social media hub for more information.
